Pseudo-code :
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:PutObject"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::app-logs-prod/*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["cloudwatch:PutMetricData"],
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:DeleteObject", "dynamodb:*"],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

Explication : On autorise explicitement PutObject sur le bucket cible et PutMetricData, et on refuse tout le reste (notamment les accès DynamoDB et les opérations de lecture/suppression S3).
